---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { allBooks } from '../lib/books';

const books = await allBooks();
const repo = 'https://github.com/markselby9/readtheplaces.com';
---

<Base
  title="Read the Places: not a map of books, a book you can walk through"
  description="An open, contributor-driven atlas of the real places in novels, presented in the order the story happens."
  ogImage="/og/mrs-dalloway.png"
>
  <div class="wrap">
    <header class="mast">
      <p class="kicker">Read the Places</p>
      <h1>Not a map of books.<br /><em>A book you can walk through.</em></h1>
      <p class="standfirst">
        An open atlas of the real places in novels, in the order the story visits them. Every place
        is pinned to a verbatim line from the book, and says how sure we are that it is the right
        place.
      </p>
    </header>

    <main id="main">
      <ul class="books">
        {
          books.map(({ slug, book, waypoints }) => (
            <li style={`--accent: ${book.palette.accent}`}>
              <a href={`/${slug}/`}>
                <span class="kicker">
                  {book.setting.city} · {book.published}
                </span>
                <h2>{book.title}</h2>
                <p class="by">{book.author}</p>
                <p class="note">{book.setting.note}</p>
                <p class="count">{waypoints.length} places →</p>
              </a>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>

      <section class="pitch">
        <h2>Why the order matters</h2>
        <p>
          A map with a chapter filter is a map of pins, and those already exist. What they cannot do
          is this. In <em>Mrs Dalloway</em>, at noon:
        </p>
        <blockquote>
          …twelve o’clock struck as Clarissa Dalloway laid her green dress on her bed, <strong
            >and the Warren Smiths walked down Harley Street.</strong
          >
        </blockquote>
        <p>
          One sentence. One stroke of the clock. Two places nearly two miles apart, two people who
          never meet, one of whom will be dead within six hours. Order is the whole difference.
        </p>

        <h2>Help build it</h2>
        <p>
          You do not need to write code to do the most valuable work here, and you will never be
          asked to upload a photograph. Adding a place means a coordinate, a verbatim quote, a
          source, and an honest label saying how sure you are. <a
            href={`${repo}/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md`}>Start here</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .books {
    list-style: none;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(18rem, 1fr));
    gap: var(--s5);
    margin-bottom: var(--s9);
  }
  .books a {
    display: block;
    padding: var(--s5);
    background: var(--paper-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s var(--ease);
  }
  .books a:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }
  .books h2 {
    font-size: var(--step-2);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-block: var(--s2) var(--s1);
  }
  .books .by,
  .books .count {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .books .note {
    margin-block: var(--s3);
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
  }
  .books .count {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .pitch {
    max-width: 38rem;
    padding-bottom: var(--s9);
  }
  .pitch h2 {
    font-size: var(--step-2);
    font-weight: 400;
    margin-block: var(--s7) var(--s4);
  }
  .pitch p {
    color: var(--ink-2);
    margin-bottom: var(--s4);
  }
  .pitch blockquote {
    color: var(--ink);
  }
</style>
